<title type="html"><![CDATA[2/4 (Thu.) Running saved my life and it might save yours/To overcome challenges, stop comparing yourself to others (May)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=470&amp;p=488#p488"><![CDATA[
4 February 2021 (Thu.) Running saved my life and it might save yours too/ To overcome challenges, stop comparing yourself to others (Host: May)<br /><br /><span style="color: #BF0000">Place: 丹堤咖啡, 台北市延平南路107號2樓 (MRT 西門站4號出口)<br />Agenda:<br />6:30-7:15 pm Free talk<br />7:15-7:50 pm Session 1 discussion<br />7:50-8:15 pm Presentation (At least two members of each table are invited, 2 mins / each member)<br />8:15-8:45 pm Session 2 discussion<br />8:45-9:00 pm Presentation</span><br /><br /><br />Session I:<br />Running Saved My Life and It Might Save Yours Too<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=x_Uw0NiseBM">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=x_Uw0NiseBM</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Points for Discussion:<br />1. Did you like PE(Physical Education) when you were in adolescence?<br />How did you go through rebellious stage or emotional disturbance? Do you have any stories to share about dealing with teenagers?<br /><br />2. The speaker does not like rules. Her teachers called her a bad kid when she was 5 years old. But she created a program on her own experience and helped many girls after many years. What are your opinions about a bad /good kid? Were you a bad /good kid when you were young ?  <br /><br />3. There is no rule for running. How do you think? How do you like running or jogging? <br /><br />4. Running can releases anxiety. How do you think of happy pace for mood? What would you do to build positive mental health/confidence when you are in a bad mood?<br /><br />5. Any action or movement starts with one step. What is your one step for specific action?  <br /><br /><br />…………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………<br />Session 2:<br />To overcome challenges, stop comparing yourself to others<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.ted.com/talks/dean_furness_to_overcome_challenges_stop_comparing_yourself_to_others">https://www.ted.com/talks/dean_furness_ ... _to_others</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Points for Discussion:<br />1.What do you know about Thoracic spinal injury? What are the problems?<br /> <br />2.The speaker shared his experience of mission impossible. How did the speech inspire you? <br /><br /><br />3. People said ‘Stop comparing yourself to others but to previous yourself.”  <br />What do you think about the maxim?<br /><br /><br /><span style="color: #BF0000">P.S.<br />1.因聚會地點是在咖啡店內，所以有低消80元喔！<br />2.參加三次後，只要繳交1000元 (學生:500元)，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />3.請帶著開放與熱情來參加自由的全英文會話聚會~</span><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=37037">JuliaHo</a> — Sat Jan 30, 2021 12:19 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
